					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>The writing seems to be of about the 13th century A.D. The inscription declares two persons Ūrbāgaṅkoṇḍa-Pērayaṉ and Nānūṟṟuva-Pērayaṉ and their descendants as the rightful holders of the <hi rend="italic">pāḍikāval</hi> (police) right of the temple of Ūrbāgaṅkoṇḍaruḻiya-Nāyanār and of the village Iṟaiyānaraiyūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śōḻakēraḷachaturvēdimaṅgalam.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
